This paper involves the development of a neural network-based evaluation function for a chess variant, Crazyhouse, which requires handling a large branching factor and state-space complexity. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
